&nbsp;
The decree of Tar Lombardy is the answer to the appeal presented last night by lawyers Luca Bauccio and Aldo Russo on behalf of the cultural association 'Moschea Essa' against the decision of the Municipality of&nbsp;Turbigo&nbsp; to deny a space for the party also leading security reasons. The 'ball' at this point passes to the Prefect. The municipality, in the light of the results of the comparison", will evaluate the adoption of the relative determinations in time useful for the start or not of the festivity" previewed for 9 and 10 April. In the decree it is specified that the Tar cannot, at this stage characterized by the extreme summariety of the judgment, adopt deliberations that would risk to replace the competent administration, without an adequate investigation and contradictory procedure, also because of the delicate evaluations to be carried out in the case of species". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
In the appeal lodged at the Tar against the decision of the Municipality of&nbsp;Turbigo&nbsp; of not granting a space for the party of end Ramadan, the lawyers representing the Islamic community had evidenced that every year in the small town in Milanese takes place "a party that attracts several hundred people called the great falo of joy". "During this feast - said to AGI lawyer Luca Bauccio, author of the recourse together with his colleague Aldo Russo - a huge bonfire is burnt, which fires several meters high and is held in an area denied though to Muslims for mysterious security problems. For the mayor of &nbsp;Turbigo&nbsp; a spectacular falo' a few meters from hundreds of people is not dangerous while swapping the wishes of end ramadan is dangerous for the public order. We're at the grotesque." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Yesterday the mayor of&nbsp;Fratelli d'Italia&nbsp;Fabrizio Allevi had communicated to the local Muslim community not to have a public space at the end of Ramadan party inviting the faithful to look for a private space "so as to be able to give rise to an event that allows the full sharing and enhancement of the tradition of the Islamic community". The lawyers of the cultural association 'Moschea Essa' have attached the photographic documentation of the falo' and the list of places considered suitable for the religious event. "We await the decision of Tar - Bauccio said - confident that this incredible story of discrimination can end positively. The rejection measure is clearly pretentious. We hope that, even in the narrowness of time, this situation will end with justice." The event is scheduled on 9 and 10 April between 7 and 10 am.&nbsp;
